  <summary>5/4/1999--Introduced.
Amends the Omnibus Crime Control and Safe Streets Act of 1968 to require that an applicant for a public safety and community policing ("cops on the beat") grant provide assurances to the Attorney General that the applicant has adopted, implemented, and is enforcing a policy that prohibits motorist stops motivated by race or other bias.</summary>
